  "prompt": "Why am I blocked from asking questions under anonymous basis on Quora?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you're blocked from asking questions anonymously on Quora:\n\n1. **Violation of Community Guidelines**: If you've previously violated Quora's policies or guidelines, your ability to ask questions anonymously may have been restricted.\n\n2. **Account Status**: If your Quora account has been flagged for unusual activity or suspicious behavior, it may impact your ability to post anonymously.\n\n3. **Technical Issues**: Sometimes, there may be technical glitches or issues with your account that affect your ability to use certain features.\n\n4. **Changes in Policy**: Quora may periodically update its policies or features, which can affect how anonymous questions can be asked.\n\nIf you believe your ability to ask questions anonymously has been restricted in error, consider reaching out to Quora's support team for clarification or assistance.",
